ğŸ“ Easy Explanation
ğŸ”¹ try
Code that may cause an exception
ğŸ”¹ catch
Handles specific exception
ğŸ”¹ finally
Always executes regardless of exception
Useful for closing resources (e.g., Scanner, file, database connection)
ğŸ”‘ One-Line Exam Answer
The finally block executes always, even if an exception occurs or is handled, ensuring cleanup or final statements run.
